data.title: What is NetViewer.exe?
data.text:
NetViewer.exe is developed by PROTECTRON according to the NetViewer.exe version information.

NetViewer.exe's description is "PROTECTRON"

NetViewer.exe is usually located in the 'C:\Program Files (x86)\NetViewer\' folder.

None of the anti-virus scanners at VirusTotal reports anything malicious about NetViewer.exe.

If you have additional information about the file, please share it with the FreeFixer users by posting a comment at the bottom of this page.

VirusTotal report

None of the 42 anti-virus programs at VirusTotal detected the NetViewer.exe file.

Error Messages

These are some of the error messages that can appear related to netviewer.exe:

netviewer.exe has encountered a problem and needs to close. We are sorry for the inconvenience.

netviewer.exe - Application Error. The instruction at "0xXXXXXXXX" referenced memory at "0xXXXXXXXX". The memory could not be "read/written". Click on OK to terminate the program.

PROTECTRON has stopped working.

End Program - netviewer.exe. This program is not responding.

netviewer.exe is not a valid Win32 application.

netviewer.exe - Application Error. The application failed to initialize properly (0xXXXXXXXX). Click OK to terminate the application.

Malware or legitimate?

If you feel that you need more information to determine if your should keep this file or remove it, please read this guide.

And now some shameless self promotion ;)
